{"id":"7261","name":"Anti-Theft","tagline":"Protect your iPhone from theft & being lost using Automation","icon":"ios14 c946986751 g59770","latest":"22436","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h5>To protect your iPhone from theft &amp; being lost you can use this Shortcut which has to be included in a Personal Automation.</h5>\n<hr>\n<ol>\n<li>Please download the Anti-Theft Shortcut Before using it in automation.</li>\n<li>After downloading the Shortcut and finish setup, follow those steps to make the automation :<ul>\n<li>Create Personal Automation &gt; Battery Level &gt; Equals 10% &gt; Add Action &gt; Search “Run Shortcut” and press on Run Shortcut to add it &gt; Press on “Shortcut” &gt; Choose “Anti-Theft” &gt; Turn off “Ask Before Running” &gt; Press “Don’t Ask” &gt; Press “Done”.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Now when the battery reaches a certain level (in this example is 10%) This Shortcut will turn on cellular data, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, Do Not Disturb, Low Power Mode &amp; turn off Airplane mode, decrease Brightness &amp; Volume level to zero then it will :<ul>\n<li>Send you a text message contains battery level &amp; current location, once you receive the message you’ll know the phone number also.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>If the iPhone is unlocked the Shortcut will also :<ul>\n<li>Send you an email contains battery level &amp; current location.</li>\n<li>Send you an email contains a 20 seconds audio recording.</li>\n<li>Save the audio recording to iCloud drive &gt; Shortcuts folder.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>After finishing all these steps the Shortcut will bring back all the settings (Brightness, Volume, Do Not Disturb, Low Power Mode) to where it was before running the Shortcut.</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<h5>If this is your first time using Shortcuts you have to activate \"<em>Allow Untrusted Shortcuts</em>\" by going to</h5>\n<p><strong>Settings -&gt; Shortcuts and enable \"Allow Untrusted Shortcuts\"</strong>.</p>\n<p>If that option is <strong>greyed out</strong>, open the Shortcuts app and run one of the starter Shortcuts or any Shortcut from the gallery . Then you should be able to enable it.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - Oct. 31, 2020, 5:35 a.m.</strong></p>"}